==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sauciness
<hw>Sau"ci*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
saucy; that which is saucy; impertinent boldness; contempt of superiors;
impudence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your <qex>sauciness</qex> will jest upon my love.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impudence; impertinence; rudeness; insolence. See
<er>Impudence</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saucisse</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Saucisson</ent>⟦br⟧
